Aim

To write a Python program to demonstrate string operations such as uppercase, lowercase, length, replace, split, join, slicing, and finding a character.

Algorithm

Start the program.
Declare a string variable text = "Hello Python".
Print the original string.
Use the upper() method to convert the string into uppercase and print it.
Use the lower() method to convert the string into lowercase and print it.
Use the len() function to find the length of the string.
Use the replace() method to replace the word "Python" with "World" and print the result.
Use the split() method to divide the string into words and print the list.
Use the join() method to join the words "Hello" and "Python" with “-” between them.
Use string slicing text[0:5] to print the first five characters.
Use the find() method to locate the position of the character "P" in the string.
Stop the program.

EXECUTION
text = "Hello Python"

print("Original:", text)
print("Uppercase:", text.upper())
print("Lowercase:", text.lower())
print("Length:", len(text))
print("Replace:", text.replace("Python", "World"))
print("Split:", text.split())
print("Join:", "-".join(["Hello", "Python"]))
print("Slice:", text[0:5])
print("Find 'P':", text.find("P"))

OUTPUT
Original: Hello Python
Uppercase: HELLO PYTHON
Lowercase: hello python
Length: 12
Replace: Hello World
Split: ['Hello', 'Python']
Join: Hello-Python
Slice: Hello
Find 'P': 6
